<%- layout('/layouts/boilerplate') %>

    <style>
        .legal-page {
            max-width: 840px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 48px 24px 80px;
            font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
            color: #1a1a2e;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .legal-page h1 {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff385c, #d90b3e);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
            margin-bottom: 6px;
        }

        .legal-page .last-updated {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            margin-bottom: 36px;
        }

        .legal-page h2 {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-top: 36px;
            color: #1a1a2e;
            border-left: 4px solid #ff385c;
            padding-left: 12px;
        }

        .legal-page p,
        .legal-page li {
            color: #444;
            font-size: 0.97rem;
        }

        .legal-page ul {
            padding-left: 22px;
        }

        .legal-page a {
            color: #ff385c;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .legal-page a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .legal-divider {
            border: none;
            border-top: 1px solid #eee;
            margin: 32px 0;
        }
    </style>

    <div class="legal-page">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: March 1, 2026</p>

        <p>Welcome to <strong>WanderLust</strong> ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
            use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our travel booking platform available at
            <a href="/">wanderlust.onrender.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p>By using WanderLust, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>

        <hr class="legal-divider">

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, and password (hashed and salted with bcrypt)
                when you register.</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> Optional details such as profile photo, bio, and social links.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Booking Data:</strong> Dates, guest count, payment method, and amount for bookings you make.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Processed securely by Razorpay and Stripe. We do not store raw
                card numbers or UPI credentials.</li>
            <li><strong>Device & Usage Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, and interaction logs
                collected via session cookies and Winston logging.</li>
            <li><strong>Uploaded Content:</strong> Images uploaded by hosts, stored securely on Cloudinary.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>To process and manage your bookings and payments.</li>
            <li>To send booking confirmation emails and PDF invoices.</li>
            <li>To send OTP verification codes for account security.</li>
            <li>To personalize your experience using AI-based recommendations.</li>
            <li>To send newsletter updates (only if you explicitly subscribed).</li>
            <li>To monitor application health and detect errors (Sentry error tracking).</li>
            <li>To comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cookies & Sessions</h2>
        <p>We use HTTP-only session cookies to keep you logged in. These cookies are stored in our MongoDB-backed
            session store and expire after 7 days of inactivity. We do not use third-party advertising cookies.</p>

